This paper deals with the classification of a large-scale audio dataset using a deep neural network with an attention mechanism. The paper focuses on a probabilistic perspective to explain the attention model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
